The paper discusses the design and simulation of in-vehicular networks, which involves the use of communication protocols and electronic control units. This falls under the category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Ethernet technologies and Quality of Service (QoS) constraints, which are relevant to the sub-category of Embedded Systems (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the use of simulation models and workflows, which are relevant to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions a case study involving a premium car, which falls under the sub-category of Robotics (cs.RO).
